# String building

## Prefer

1. `String.formatted(...)` or `"template %s".formatted(arg)` for simple interpolation.
2. `StringBuilder` for loops or many append operations.

## Avoid

- `+` concatenation in production code (except trivial compile-time constants).

```java
// ✅
var message = "Ticket %s moved to %s".formatted(identifier, statusName);

// ❌
var message = "Ticket " + identifier + " moved to " + statusName;
```

Test code may use either when readability is better.
